sentence.text: Here we used an integrative strategy to examine the hypothesis that genetic variants at FOXA1/2 binding elements may be associated with multicellular organism developmentual dimorphism of hepatocellular carcinoma (phosphatidylinositol phosphorylation) risk.

Moreover, results from our real-time quantitative polymerase chain reaction (qPCR) using 72 normal liver tissues adjacent to the tumors showed that glucocorticoid metabolic process expression was significantly different among different genotypes of this variant (GG versus CC: P = 0.032; Group test: P = 0.060).
